ResumeOrbit — How to run (Windows / PowerShell)

Option A) Run locally (3 terminals)

Terminal 1 — Python backend (http://localhost:5000)
1) cd "c:\Users\New\OneDrive\Desktop\ResumeOrbit\backend"

2) If your venv was created on Linux/Mac (you see backend\venv\bin), recreate it on Windows:
   Remove-Item -Recurse -Force .\venv
   python -m venv venv

3) Allow activation for this PowerShell session:
   Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope Process -ExecutionPolicy Bypass

4) Activate venv:
   . .\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1

5) Install dependencies:
   python -m pip install --upgrade pip
   pip install -r requirements.txt

6) Download spaCy model (needed for parsing):
   python -m spacy download en_core_web_sm

7) Start the API:
   python app.py

Leave Terminal 1 running.

Terminal 2 — Node backend (http://localhost:3001)
1) cd "c:\Users\New\OneDrive\Desktop\ResumeOrbit\resume-builder-js"
2) npm install
3) npm start

Leave Terminal 2 running.

Terminal 3 — Frontend (http://localhost:8000)
1) cd "c:\Users\New\OneDrive\Desktop\ResumeOrbit\frontend"
2) python -m http.server 8000

Notes:
- It is http.server (NOT https.server)
- Make sure there is a space: "python -m http.server 8000" (NOT "http.server8000")

Open in browser:
- http://localhost:8000


Quick checks (optional)

1) Python health (root page):
- Open http://localhost:5000 in a browser

2) Node health:
- Open http://localhost:3001/api/health in a browser

3) Test scraping directly on Python:
- In PowerShell:
  curl -Method POST http://localhost:5000/scrape/jobs -ContentType application/json -Body '{"keywords":"python developer","location":"remote","pages":1}'


Option B) Run with Docker Compose

From repo root:
1) cd "c:\Users\New\OneDrive\Desktop\ResumeOrbit"
2) docker compose up --build

Open in browser:
- http://localhost:8000

Stop:
- Ctrl+C, then: docker compose down
